  "text": "While most species distribution models are built with species presence-absence or community composition data, we used high-resolution maps of ecosystems to characterize the climate space of a dependent class variable. Ecosystem delineations for the continental USA and Canada west of 1008 latitude were compiled from various public data sources (as described in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ). Species frequencies and probabilities of presence were calculated for each ecological region based on 55 743 forest inventory plot records within the ecoregion boundaries (as described in [CITATION_3] ). The ecosystem-based modelling approach was chosen for its high model specificity (i.e. low tendency to overpredict), while maintaining reasonable model sensitivity. This was particularly advantageous when approaching climate combinations that are not well represented in model training data [CITATION_4] .",
